&gt; What if the setup logic involves connecting to databases and 
&gt; running queries that tends to be a bit slow for doing on every 
&gt; single test?  Is an explanation available anywhere on the web 
&gt; telling how to get tests to run faster by executing slow 
&gt; initialization code only once before all the tests?

Stephen,

What you want to do is create a class that extends TestSetup.  
TestSetups allow you to do some initilization/de-initilization around 
a test suite just as you described.

class MyTestSetup extends TestSetup {
  public MyTestSetup( Test t ) {
    super(t);
  }

  protected void setUp() {
    Connection = DriverManager.getConnection(&quot;jdbc:url&quot;);
  }

  protected void tearDown() {
  }
}

class MyTest extends TestCase {
  public MyTest( String name ) {
    super( name );
  }

  public void testOne() {
  }

  public static Test suite() {
     return new MyTestSetup( new TestSuite( MyTest.class ) );
  }

  public static void main( String args[] ) {
     TestRunner.run( suite() );
  }
}





